{
  "_comment": [
    "==========================================================================",
    " D2 H5 Text Game — Asset Mapping (art-director, append-only)",
    "==========================================================================",
    "",
    " Purpose:",
    "   Flat resolver from a gameplay ID's stable suffix to the public URL of",
    "   a painted asset under public/assets/d2/generated/. Consumed by the UI",
    "   layer; the engine never reads this file. Treat as append-only — when",
    "   new art lands, add a key; do NOT rename or delete existing keys.",
    "",
    " Key convention:",
    "   - The gameplay layer uses fully-qualified IDs of the form",
    "       <category-prefix>/<key>",
    "     for example: 'monsters/act1.fallen', 'items/unique.shako',",
    "     'classes/barbarian', 'zones/act1.rogue-encampment',",
    "     'mercs/act1-rogue-pierce'.",
    "   - This map's keys are the trailing <key> segment after the slash.",
    "     The UI strips the category prefix before lookup. This keeps the",
    "     map flat and lets us share keys cleanly across categories.",
    "   - Asset filenames mirror the engine ID with dots:",
    "       monsters/act1.fallen  ->  monsters.act1.fallen.png",
    "       items/unique.shako    ->  items.unique.shako.png",
    "     except bosses live under monsters/bosses.* in the manifest; the",
    "     mapping hides this — UI always queries by 'act1.andariel' etc.",
    "",
    " Fallback semantics:",
    "   - string  -> use this URL directly.",
    "   - null    -> intentionally absent; UI shows the silhouette.",
    "   - missing -> bug; UI shows silhouette and warns in dev.",
    "",
    " Mercs:",
    "   Hireable mercs have dedicated portrait keys such as",
    "   'act1.rogue-fire' and 'act3.iron-wolf-lightning', generated from",
    "   class-portraits/mercs.act<N>.<slug>.png. The UI should try the",
    "   exact dedicated key first, then fall back to archetype proxy keys",
    "   (rogue-archer, desert-mercenary, iron-wolf, barbarian-warrior)",
    "   for legacy/non-hireable mercs without dedicated art.",
    "",
    " Style: paths are absolute under the public/ root, served from /. No",
    " trailing query strings; UI may append cache-busting if needed.",
    "=========================================================================="
  ],

  "version": 1,

  "classes": {
